'''Andrey Dmitriyevich Arkhangelsky''' ({{lang-ru|Андре́й Дми́триевич Арха́нгельский}}) (December 8, 1879 – June 16, 1940) was a [[Russia]]n geologist. He was a professor at [[Moscow State University]].

He won the [[Lenin Prize]] in 1928.

==Memoria==
A [[impact crater|crater]] on [[Mars]] and [[Arkhangel'skiy Nunataks]] in [[Antarctica]] are named after him.

