{{Infobox book |name = Finding Darwin's God |title_orig = Finding Darwin's God: A Scientist's Search for Common Ground Between God and Evolution |translator = |image = Finding Darwin's God cover.jpg |image_size = 150px |caption = Finding Darwin's God first edition cover |author = [[Kenneth R. Miller]] |illustrator = |cover_artist = |country = United States |language = English |series = |subject = [[Creationism]], [[evolution]] and the [[creation-evolution controversy]] |genre = Non-fiction |publisher = Cliff Street Books |pub_date = 1999 |english_pub_date = 1999 |media_type = Print (hardcover) |pages = 338 |isbn = 0-06-017593-1 |oclc = |preceded_by = |followed_by = }} '''''Finding Darwin's God: A Scientist's Search for Common Ground Between God and Evolution''''' is a 2000 book by the American [[cell biologist]] and [[Roman Catholic]] [[Kenneth R. Miller]] wherein he argues that [[evolution]] does not contradict religious faith. Miller argues that evolution occurred, that the earth is not [[young earth creationism|young]], that science must work based on [[methodological naturalism]], and that evolution cannot be construed as an effective argument for [[atheism]].<ref>{{cite news |author= Henry E. Neufeld |title=Finding Darwin's God |url=http://energion.com/books/reviews/finding_darwin.shtml |publisher=Energion |accessdate=2008-05-02 }}</ref>
