{{Infobox radio show |show_name = Science in Action |image = |imagesize = |caption = |other_names = |format = Current science |runtime = 28 minutes |country = UK |language = English |home_station = BBC World Service |syndicates = |television = |presenter = Roland Pease |starring = |announcer = |creator = |writer = |director = |senior_editor = |editor = |producer = |exec_producer = |narrated = |rec_location = [[Broadcasting House]] |first_aired = 7 July 1979 |last_aired = |num_series = |num_episodes = |audio_format = |opentheme = |othertheme = |endtheme = |website = [http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p002vsnb Science in Action] |podcast = [http://www.bbc.co.uk/podcasts/series/scia Podcasts] }}
'''''Science in Action''''' is a long-running weekly radio programme produced by the [[BBC World Service]] and currently hosted by British journalists Roland Pease<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://journalisted.com/roland-pease |title=Roland Pease |publisher=Media Standards Trust|website=journa''listed'' |language=en |access-date=2018-04-03}}</ref> and Marnie Chesterton, and scientist and broadcaster Professor [[Adam Hart]]. It is broadcast on Thursdays at 18.32 [[GMT]] and repeated twice the following day, at 01.32 and 08.32.
A programme with the title ''Science in Action'' is believed to have begun life in 1964, when it replaced an earlier series, dating from the 1950s, called ''Science and Industry''.<ref>{{Cite web | title = BBC radio science: challenges and opportunities | publisher = Journal of Science Communication (JCOM) | accessdate = 2011-04-05 | url = http://jcom.sissa.it/archive/03/04/C030401/C030405 }}</ref> From September 1965 a short-lived series called ''Science in Action'' ran on the [[BBC Home Service|Home Service]]; it was broadcast at 19.30 on Thursdays, later 21.30. In December 1965 it was moved to 14.30 on Fridays. The present weekly World Service series, also called ''Science in Action'', began on Saturday 7 July 1979.
